7">Exercise 3</a></p></li></ol></li></ol>
</div></div>


<h2 id=3D"hid2" class=3D"subsection">Definition</h2>
<p>
   Here is a definition.
</p>
<div class=3D"definition">
   <p><span class=3D"titoletto">Definition</span>
      Let
      <span class=3D"inm"><img class=3D"sp" width=3D"13" height=3D"25" src=
=3D"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAANvf7wAAACH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAA=
AICRAEAOw=3D=3D" alt=3D"X" style=3D"background-position:0px -2943px;vertica=
l-align:-5px"></span>
      be a
      <span class=3D"inm"><img class=3D"sp" width=3D"39" height=3D"25" src=
=3D"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAANvf7wAAACH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAA=
AICRAEAOw=3D=3D" alt=3D"Kx1" style=3D"background-position:0px -2457px;verti=
cal-align:-5px"></span>
       <a href=3D"https://www.statlect.com/fundamentals-of-probability/rand=
om-vectors#rand">random vector</a>. The covariance matrix of
      <span class=3D"inm"><img class=3D"sp" width=3D"13" height=3D"25" src=
=3D"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAANvf7wAAACH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAA=
AICRAEAOw=3D=3D" alt=3D"X" style=3D"background-position:0px -2943px;vertica=
l-align:-5px"></span>,
      or variance-covariance matrix of
      <span class=3D"inm"><img class=3D"sp" width=3D"13" height=3D"25" src=
=3D"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAANvf7wAAACH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAA=
AICRAEAOw=3D=3D" alt=3D"X" style=3D"background-position:0px -2943px;vertica=
l-align:-5px"></span>,
      denoted by
      <span class=3D"inm"><img class=3D"sp" width=3D"47" height=3D"26" src=
=3D"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAANvf7wAAACH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAA=
AICRAEAOw=3D=3D" alt=3D"[eq1]" style=3D"background-position:0px -2287px;ver=
tical-align:-5px"></span>,
      is defined as
      follows:<span class=3D"displayed"><img class=3D"sp" width=3D"250" hei=
ght=3D"41" src=3D"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAANvf7wAAACH5BAEAAAA=
ALAAAAAABAAEAAAICRAEAOw=3D=3D" alt=3D"[eq2]" style=3D"background-position:0=
px -635px;"></span>provided
      the above  <a href=3D"https://www.statlect.com/fundamentals-of-probab=
ility/expected-value#exva">expected values</a> exist and are
      well-defined.
   </p>
</div>
<p>
   It is a multivariate generalization of the definition of
    <a href=3D"https://www.statlect.com/fundamentals-of-probability/varianc=
e">variance</a> for a scalar random variable
   <span class=3D"inm"><img class=3D"sp" width=3D"11" height=3D"24" src=3D"=
data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAANvf7wAAACH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAICR=
AEAOw=3D=3D" alt=3D"Y" style=3D"background-position:0px -2992px;vertical-al=
ign:-5px"></span>:<span class=3D"displayed"><img class=3D"sp2" width=3D"353=
" height=3D"40" src=3D"https://www.statlect.com/images/covariance-matrix__8=
.png" alt=3D"[eq3]"></span>
</p>
<h2 id=3D"hid3" class=3D"subsection">Structure</h2>
<p>
   Let
   <span class=3D"inm"><img class=3D"sp" width=3D"21" height=3D"24" src=3D"=
data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAANvf7wAAACH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAICR=
AEAOw=3D=3D" alt=3D"X_1" style=3D"background-position:0px -2653px;vertical-=
align:-5px"></span>,
   ...,
   <span class=3D"inm"><img class=3D"sp" width=3D"22" height=3D"24" src=3D"=
data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAANvf7wAAACH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAICR=
AEAOw=3D=3D" alt=3D"$X_{K}$" style=3D"background-position:0px -2629px;verti=
cal-align:-5px"></span>
   denote the
   <span class=3D"inm"><img class=3D"sp" width=3D"14" height=3D"24" src=3D"=
data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAANvf7wAAACH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAICR=
AEAOw=3D=3D" alt=3D"K" style=3D"background-position:0px -2895px;vertical-al=
ign:-5px"></span>
   components of the vector
   <span class=3D"inm"><img class=3D"sp" width=3D"13" height=3D"25" src=3D"=
data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAANvf7wAAACH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAICR=
AEAOw=3D=3D" alt=3D"X" style=3D"background-position:0px -2943px;vertical-al=
ign:-5px"></span>.
</p>
<p>
   From the definition of
   <span class=3D"inm"><img class=3D"sp" width=3D"47" height=3D"26" src=3D"=
data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAANvf7wAAACH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAICR=
AEAOw=3D=3D" alt=3D"[eq4]" style=3D"background-position:0px -2287px;vertica=
l-align:-5px"></span>,
   it can easily be seen that
   <span class=3D"inm"><img class=3D"sp" width=3D"47" height=3D"26" src=3D"=
data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAANvf7wAAACH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAICR=
AEAOw=3D=3D" alt=3D"[eq5]" style=3D"background-position:0px -2287px;vertica=
l-align:-5px"></span>
   is a
   <span class=3D"inm"><img class=3D"sp" width=3D"42" height=3D"24" src=3D"=
data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAANvf7wAAACH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAICR=
AEAOw=3D=3D" alt=3D"$K	imes K$" style=3D"background-position:0px -2337px;ve=
rtical-align:-5px"></span>
   matrix with the following
   <a id=3D"struct"></a>structure:<span class=3D"displayed"><img class=3D"s=
p2" width=3D"550" height=3D"288" src=3D"https://www.statlect.com/images/cov=
ariance-matrix__16.png" alt=3D"[eq6]"></span>
</p>
<p>
   Therefore, the covariance matrix of
   <span class=3D"inm"><img class=3D"sp" width=3D"13" height=3D"25" src=3D"=
data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAANvf7wAAACH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAICR=
AEAOw=3D=3D" alt=3D"X" style=3D"background-position:0px -2943px;vertical-al=
ign:-5px"></span>
   is a square
   <span class=3D"inm"><img class=3D"sp" width=3D"42" height=3D"24" src=3D"=
data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAANvf7wAAACH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAICR=
AEAOw=3D=3D" alt=3D"$K	imes K$" style=3D"background-position:0px -2337px;ve=
rtical-align:-5px"></span>
   matrix whose generic
   <span class=3D"inm"><img class=3D"sp" width=3D"31" height=3D"25" src=3D"=
data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAANvf7wAAACH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAICR=
AEAOw=3D=3D" alt=3D"$left( i,j
ight) $" style=3D"background-position:0px -2604px;vertical-align:-5px"></sp=
an>-th
   entry is equal to the  <a href=3D"https://www.statlect.com/fundamentals-=
of-probability/covariance">covariance</a> between
   <span class=3D"inm"><img class=3D"sp" width=3D"18" height=3D"24" src=3D"=
data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAANvf7wAAACH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAICR=
AEAOw=3D=3D" alt=3D"X_i" style=3D"background-position:0px -2871px;vertical-=
align:-5px"></span>
   and
   <span class=3D"inm"><img class=3D"sp" width=3D"18" height=3D"26" src=3D"=
data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAANvf7wAAACH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAICR=
AEAOw=3D=3D" alt=3D"$X_{j}$" style=3D"background-position:0px -2845px;verti=
cal-align:-5px"></span>.
</p>
<p>
   Since
   <span class=3D"inm"><img class=3D"sp" width=3D"145" height=3D"25" src=3D=
"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAANvf7wAAACH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIC=
RAEAOw=3D=3D" alt=3D"[eq7]" style=3D"background-position:0px -1684px;vertic=
al-align:-5px"></span>
   when
   <span class=3D"inm"><img class=3D"sp" width=3D"33" height=3D"25" src=3D"=
data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAANvf7wAAACH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAICR=
AEAOw=3D=3D" alt=3D"$i=3Dj$" style=3D"background-position:0px -2579px;verti=
cal-align:-5px"></span>,
   the diagonal entries of the covariance matrix are equal to the variances=
 of
   the individual entries of
   <span class=3D"inm"><img class=3D"sp" width=3D"13" height=3D"25" src=3D"=
data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAANvf7wAAACH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAICR=
AEAOw=3D=3D" alt=3D"X" style=3D"background-position:0px -2943px;vertical-al=
ign:-5px"></span>.
</p>
<h2 id=3D"hid4" class=3D"subsection">Example</h2>
<p>
   Here is an example.
</p>
<p>
   Suppose that
   <span class=3D"inm"><img class=3D"sp" width=3D"13" height=3D"25" src=3D"=
data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAANvf7wAAACH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAICR=
AEAOw=3D=3D" alt=3D"X" style=3D"background-position:0px -2943px;vertical-al=
ign:-5px"></span>
   is a
   <span class=3D"inm"><img class=3D"sp" width=3D"36" height=3D"24" src=3D"=
data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAANvf7wAAACH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAICR=
AEAOw=3D=3D" alt=3D"$2	imes 1$" style=3D"background-position:0px -2506px;ve=
rtical-align:-5px"></span>
   random vector with components
   <span class=3D"inm"><img class=3D"sp" width=3D"21" height=3D"24" src=3D"=
data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAANvf7wAAACH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAICR=
AEAOw=3D=3D" alt=3D"X_1" style=3D"background-position:0px -2653px;vertical-=
align:-5px"></span>
   and
   <span class=3D"inm"><img class=3D"sp" width=3D"21" height=3D"24" src=3D"=
data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAANvf7wAAACH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAICR=
AEAOw=3D=3D" alt=3D"X_2" style=3D"background-position:0px -2725px;vertical-=
align:-5px"></span>.
