AEAOw=3D=3D" alt=3D"[eq5]" style=3D"background-position:0px -2287px;vertica=
l-align:-5px"></span>
   is a  <a href=3D"https://www.statlect.com/matrix-algebra/positive-defini=
te-matrix">positive-semidefinite
   matrix</a>, that is, for any
   <span class=3D"inm"><img class=3D"sp" width=3D"39" height=3D"24" src=3D"=
data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAANvf7wAAACH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAICR=
AEAOw=3D=3D" alt=3D"$1	imes K$" style=3D"background-position:0px -2433px;ve=
rtical-align:-5px"></span>
   vector
   <span class=3D"inm"><img class=3D"sp" width=3D"11" height=3D"24" src=3D"=
data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAANvf7wAAACH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAICR=
AEAOw=3D=3D" alt=3D"a" style=3D"background-position:0px -3040px;vertical-al=
ign:-5px"></span>:<span class=3D"displayed"><img class=3D"sp" width=3D"114"=
 height=3D"38" src=3D"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAANvf7wAAACH5BAE=
AAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAICRAEAOw=3D=3D" alt=3D"[eq26]" style=3D"background-posit=
ion:0px -1900px;"></span>
</p>

<div class=3D"bproof"><span class=3D"bproof">Proof</span></div>
<div id=3D"idn5" class=3D"clps"><div class=3D"proofline">
<p>This is easily proved by using the
    <a href=3D"https://www.statlect.com/fundamentals-of-probability/covaria=
nce-matrix#mult">Multiplication by constant matrices</a> property
   above:<span class=3D"displayed"><img class=3D"sp" width=3D"187" height=
=3D"38" src=3D"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAANvf7wAAACH5BAEAAAAALA=
AAAAABAAEAAAICRAEAOw=3D=3D" alt=3D"[eq27]" style=3D"background-position:0px=
 -1062px;"></span>where
   the last inequality follows from the fact that variance is always positi=
ve.
</p>
</div></div>
